&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 2 Clinical Support Worker&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen within the respiratory department at St James Hospital for band 2 clinical support workers. We are looking to recruit motivated, caring and compassionate individuals to support our nursing teams to deliver a high standard of care to our patients. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;You will be actively involved in providing direct and indirect personal and clinical care for patients under the supervision of a registered nurse within each speciality.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Applicants must hold a Level 2 vocational qualification in health and social care or an equivalent healthcare related qualification.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;You must also have experience of working in a health care setting.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Come and join our team in Leeds and become part of ‘The Leeds Way’ sharing our vision and values. Our Trust is recognised for our staff engagement, great care and rated &lt;strong&gt;GOOD&lt;/strong&gt; by the Care Quality Commission.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Leeds Teaching Hospitals NHS Trust is one of the largest acute health providers in the UK and based in one of the fastest growing and vibrant cities in the north.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;For all new starters to the Trust we have an award winning, structured Introduction to Professional Practice (IPP) Induction programme to prepare you for working at LTHT. Within the first three months of your role you will be required to complete the Cavendish Care Certificate.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Interviews will take place virtually in line with COVID-19 guidelines.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For more information please contact: - rachel.metcalfe1@nhs.net or sue.whiteley1@nhs.net&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Internal care support staff&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;em&gt; currently employed by Leeds Teaching Hospitals NHS Trust, who wish to work in a different area, at the same AfC Band, job description and person specification should contact their Matron and employ the internal transfer process.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;em&gt;We may share information, as appropriate, that you have provided in your application form with external partners or other organisations help to facilitate your recruitment process.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
